"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654537","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-14","<p>Support for those seeking to start and grow a business is available online at Gov.uk or from the National Business Support Helpline which provides signposting, diagnostic support and advice on a range of issues. The service can be accessed by telephone on 0300 456 3565 or via webchat, email, Twitter, Facebook and YouTube. There are 39 Growth Hubs across England which join up local and national business support for businesses in their area. Northamptonshire businesses have access to the Northamptonshire Growth Hub and South East Midland’s Velocity. The Midlands Engine Investment Fund, due to be launched in 2017 (subject to final funding arrangements), is expected to provide over £250m of support to the region’s 460,000 smaller businesses. The British Business Bank and Innovate UK also provide assistance to support business growth.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-12-14T11:06:04.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654537/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654537/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654537/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-12-07","Economic Growth","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to support business growth in (a) Northamptonshire and (b) England.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","56685"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654538","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-20","<p>The Higher Education and Research Bill and white paper set out the high level framework for the UK Research and Innovation (UKRI) governance arrangements. Subject to the will of parliament, the final arrangements will be refined and agreed in partnership with the UKRI Chief Executive and Board once appointed. These arrangements will follow best practice for non-departmental public bodies and managing public money guidance, and will be published once agreed.</p><p>Additional information on the vision, principles and governance of UKRI can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/559210/Higher_Education_and_Research_Bill-UKRI_Vision_Factsheet.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/559210/Higher_Education_and_Research_Bill-UKRI_Vision_Factsheet.pdf</a></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-12-20T11:43:32.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654538/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654538/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654538/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-12-07","UK Research and Innovation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the governance arrangements will be for UK Research and Innovation.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","56686"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654539","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-16","I refer the hon Member for Great Grimsby to the answer I gave her on 12 December, UIN: 56446.","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-16T14:57:35.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654539/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654539/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654539/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-12-07","Fisheries: Norway","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether he discussed the future of the UK fishing industry with the Norwegian Foreign Minister during his recent visit to the UK.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","56430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654540","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-12","<p>My Rt hon Friend the Secretary of State discussed a range of topics with the Norwegian Minister of Foreign Affairs on his recent visit. It included the UK’s Commitments at the World Trade Organization and how the UK and Norway can continue to build our trade relationship. Fisheries and seafood trade work is led by the Department for the Environment, Food and Rural Affairs.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-12T14:53:58.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654540/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654540/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654540/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-12-07","Seafood: Overseas Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, whether he held discussions on the potential effect of tariffs on the seafood trade between Britain and Norway with the Norwegian Foreign Minister during his recent visit to the UK.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","56446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654541","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-12","<p>I refer the hon Member for Brent North to the answer given by my hon Friend, the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for International Trade, to the hon Member for Birmingham, Hall Green on 6 December; UIN:55925.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-12T14:54:44.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654541/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654541/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654541/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-12-07","Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, with reference to his oral evidence to the European Scrutiny Committee on 26 October 2016, on Parliamentary Scrutiny of EU Trade Deal: Canada/EU Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement, HC 792, for what reasons a debate on that agreement did not take place in the House in November 2016.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","56676"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654542","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-12-15","<p>The Government wants to give UK companies the maximum freedom to trade with and operate in the Single Market – and let European businesses do the same here.The Department for Exiting the European Union, working with officials across government, continues to undertake wide-ranging data analysis looking at over 50 sectors as well as cross-cutting regulatory issues. The Department is also engaging widely with representatives from sectors. This work will inform the UK's position for the upcoming negotiations with our EU partners.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-12-15T15:46:21.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654542/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654542/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654542/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-12-07","Import Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what recent assessment he has made of the potential effect of reverting to default World Trade Organisation tariffs on UK businesses; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","56684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654543","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-16","<p>Ministers constantly meet with businesses and representatives from across the UK, including the West Midlands, and will continue to do so.</p><p>The export of goods increased last quarter in the West Midlands by 17.8% compared to the same quarter the previous year, which was the second highest increase across all English regions. The count of exporters also rose by 3.4% to 11, 801 in the same period.</p><p> </p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2016-12-16T14:29:36.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654543/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654543/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654543/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-12-07","Business: West Midlands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many representatives of businesses in the West Midlands he has met since his Department was created; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","56636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654544","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-16","<p>The Department for International Trade already has a strong and capable trade policy team, which has more than doubled in size since 23 June and is continuing to grow. Over the coming months, we will be developing the Trade Policy team, to build the world class negotiating strengths needed, to deliver the best outcomes for the UK. They will have the depth and breadth of expertise to handle the full range of sectoral and cross-cutting issues that arise in trade agreements, supported by analysts and lawyers. We will continue to hire the brightest and best talent from within the UK civil service and, in time, will look to enhance our team, by drawing on expertise from elsewhere.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-16T14:53:59.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654544/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654544/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654544/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-12-07","Trade Agreements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many specialist trade negotiators are employed by his Department; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","56637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654545","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-16","<p>In the Department for International Trade, there are nine civil servants working full-time on matters related to the World Trade Organisation. They are supported by officials working in other Departments, including the Department for Exiting the European Union, the Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs and the Foreign and Commonwealth Office.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-16T12:15:41.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654545/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654545/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654545/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-12-07","World Trade Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many civil servants in his Department are working full-time with the World Trade Organisation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","56584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654546","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-16","<p>The Prime Minister announced the creation of the Department for International Trade on the 13 July 2016. The budget for the new Department is being finalised and will be set out in the Supplementary Estimate.</p><p>We are currently establishing whether we need to call upon external support as part of the internal planning round for the 17/18 Financial Year.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-16T12:25:52.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654546/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654546/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654546/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-12-07","Department for International Trade: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many third party (a) consultants and (b) consultancy companies his Department plans to commission; and what the cost to the public purse of such commissioning will be in (i) 2017, (ii) 2018, (iii) 2019 and (iv) 2020.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","56644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654547","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-16","<p>The Prime Minister announced the creation of the Department for International Trade (DIT) on the 14th July 2016.</p><p> </p><p>I refer the hon Member for Tottenham to the answer I gave to the hon Member for Hornsey and Wood Green on 17 October, UIN47214, for details of the consulting companies the Department has made use of since it was established.</p><p> </p><p>Since that answer was provided, UK Export Finance (UKEF) has used SFW Ltd for consultancy services for an “Electronic Document Management” review (£15,736k) and ANSEC IA Ltd for an “Information Assurance” review (£22,900). UKEF’s costs are on-going service delivery costs which are not connected with machinery of government changes.</p><p> </p><p>DIT and UK Export Finance will be publishing Workforce Management Information, which details the number and cost of non-payroll staff, those classed as contingent labour consultants and consultancy on:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=Workforce+Management+Information&amp;publication_filter_option=transparency-data&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=all&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date=" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=Workforce+Management+Information&amp;publication_filter_option=transparency-data&amp;topics%5B%5D=all&amp;departments%5B%5D=all&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5B%5D=all&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date=</a></p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-16T14:59:51.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654547/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654547/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654547/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-12-07","Department for International Trade: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many third party (a) consultants and (b) consulting companies have been commissioned by his Department since it was established; and what the cost to the public purse of such commissioning has been.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","56642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654548","Department for International Trade","false","2016-12-16","<p>The Department for International Trade (DIT) has a statutory requirement to publish information on the gender pay gap amongst its employees under the Equality Act 2010 (Specific Duties, Gender Pay Gap Information and Public Authorities) Regulations 2016, which come into force on 6 April 2017.</p><p> </p><p>The information will be published no later than 4 April 2018 as required by the Regulations. DIT and UK Export Finance will publish their information separately on their respective gov.uk sites.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2016-12-16T14:52:12.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654548/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654548/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654548/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2016-12-07","Department for International Trade: Equal Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what plans his Department has to publish information on the gender pay gap among its employees.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","56607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654549","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-12-16","<p>The latest gender pay gap data (published in October earlier this year) can be found on the Office for National Statistics website. Due to the timings of the data collection DExEU was was not included in this exercise but this information can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016" target="_blank">https://www.ons.gov.uk/employmentandlabourmarket/peopleinwork/publicsectorpersonnel/bulletins/civilservicestatistics/2016</a></p><p>In October 2015, the then Prime Minister announced that new gender pay gap reporting measures being introduced across the private and voluntary sector from April 2017 would be extended to also apply across the public sector. We are actively working to ensure the gender pay gap data we report in future fully mirrors these new requirements.</p><p>The Civil Service has a comprehensive plan to become the most inclusive employer in the UK. This is called the Talent Action Plan and was refreshed in March 2016. The plan commits the Civil Service to a number of actions with the aim of removing barriers faced by underrepresented groups, including women, from succeeding. The plan sets out the ambition under key themes which includes recruitment and selection, talent and progression, inclusive culture and social mobility.</p><p>Key actions include ensuring single gender panels in recruitment and shortlists are now by exception only (as committed in the first publication of the Talent Action Plan) and committing the Civil Service to reviewing the way in which talent is defined and identified to ensure more inclusive ways to identify potential are developed.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-12-16T16:23:17.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654549/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654549/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654549/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-12-07","Department for Exiting the European Union: Equal Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what plans his Department has to publish information on the gender pay gap among its employees.","false","Biography information for Jake Berry","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","56602"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654550","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-12-12","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on 1 December 2016 to Question 55210 and 55211 which provides details on consultancy companies engaged by the Department.</p><p>Going forward, the Department will make further use of external support and recruitment as appropriate to ensure it has the right expertise to deliver its objectives.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","56643","2016-12-12T16:29:19.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654550/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654550/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654550/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-12-07","Department for Exiting the European Union: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many third party (a) consultants and (b) consultancy companies his Department plans to commission; and what the cost to the public purse of such commissioning will be in (i) 2017, (ii) 2018, (iii) 2019 and (iv) 2020.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","56645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654551","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-12-12","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given on 1 December 2016 to Question 55210 and 55211 which provides details on consultancy companies engaged by the Department.</p><p>Going forward, the Department will make further use of external support and recruitment as appropriate to ensure it has the right expertise to deliver its objectives.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones","56645","2016-12-12T16:29:19.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654551/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654551/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654551/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-12-07","Department for Exiting the European Union: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, how many third party (a) consultants and (b) consultancy companies have been commissioned by his Department since it was established; and what the cost to the public purse of such commissioning has been.","false","Biography information for Mr David Lammy","Tottenham","Mr David Lammy","56643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654552","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-12-15","<p>We want to give British companies the maximum freedom to trade and operate in the single market – and let European businesses do the same here.</p><p>We have been clear that we will pursue a solution that works for the unique circumstances of the UK. Ministers are considering the UK’s future customs and trading relations with the EU and work continues to analyse the options to ensure we have the best possible outcome for the UK.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2016-12-15T15:47:35.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654552/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654552/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654552/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-12-07","Exports: Transitional Arrangements","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what assessment the Government has made of the transitional support that would be required for exporting companies based in the UK for a future outside the (a) Single Market and (b) customs union.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","56638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654553","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-12-12","<p>We have already started a wide-ranging programme of engagement in order to build a national consensus, listening to organisations, institutions and companies in as many sectors as possible to establish their priorities and understand their concerns, and also to hear what they think the solutions could be. These discussions will inform our negotiating position; it would not be in the national interest to give a running commentary.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-12-12T16:22:22.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654553/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654553/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654553/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-12-07","Fisheries: Norway","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether he discussed the future of the UK fishing industry with the Norwegian Foreign Minister during his recent visit to the UK.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","56445"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654554","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-12-12","<p>As we conduct our negotiations to leave the EU, we will aim to obtain the best deal for consumers on roaming, to support participation in a single market for digital goods and services.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-12-12T17:08:33.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654554/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654554/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654554/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-12-07","Mobile Phones: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the potential effect on European mobile data roaming charges for UK citizens of the UK leaving the EU; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","56454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654555","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-12-12","<p>The Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union met with the Norwegian Foreign Minister on 5 December. They discussed our work towards an orderly withdrawal of the UK from the EU.</p>","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-12-12T16:27:35.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654555/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654555/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654555/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-12-07","Seafood: Overseas Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether he had discussions on the potential effect of tariffs on the seafood trade between Britain and Norway with the Norwegian Foreign Minister during his recent visit to the UK.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","56431"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654556","Home Office","false","2016-12-19","<p>There are a number of options as to how EU migration might work once we have left the European Union. We are considering various options and it would be wrong to set out further positions at this stage.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-12-19T16:09:01.45Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654556/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654556/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654556/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-07","Immigration Controls: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate her Department has made of the extra resources needed at ports to process the arrival of EU citizens following the UK's withdrawal from the EU.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","56432"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654557","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2016-12-12","As the UK is party to the EEA agreement only in its capacity as an EU member state, once we leave the European Union the EEA agreement will automatically cease to apply to the UK.","Clwyd West","Mr David Jones",,"2016-12-12T16:20:23.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654557/answer","Biography information for Mr David Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654557/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654557/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2016-12-07","European Economic Area: Membership","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what the Government's policy is on whether Article 127 of the EEA agreement should be triggered.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","56529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654924","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-13","<p>The Department for Transport continually monitors the development of rail technology. The high costs of conventional magnetic levitation trains and their incompatibility with existing rail networks are likely to limit the market opportunities for this technology. We are however also assessing the potential for the development of hyperloop technologies in the UK which may also use magnetic levitation. The Department’s Science Advisory Council intends to publish a paper on hyperloop in early 2017 setting out its position on the technical credibility of the concept and the opportunities it offers to UK industry given our technology and engineering expertise.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2016-12-13T11:43:00.44Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654924/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654924/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/654924/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-07","Railways: Technology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has assessed the potential merits of developing magnetic levitation trains as part of the Government's industrial strategy.","false","Biography information for Andrew Selous","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","907831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657460","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-13","<p>Business growth in the North of England is a priority for this Government. There are now over 167,000 more businesses in the North than in 2010, an increase of over 15%.</p><p> </p><p>As part of our Northern Powerhouse Strategy we are supporting investment funds totalling over £500m for SMEs, four further science and innovation audits, and 11 Growth Hubs in the North.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-12-13T17:12:18.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657460/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657460/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657460/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-12-07","Business: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he has taken to support business growth in the north of England.","false","Biography information for Graham Evans","Weaver Vale","Graham Evans","907839"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657461","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-13","<p>I receive regular correspondence from individuals and organisations concerning the rights of workers, including agency workers. The status and rights of agency workers are being examined further by Matthew Taylor in his review of modern working practices. In considering their position he will be engaging with workers, employers, trade unions and representative bodies over the coming months.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Stourbridge","Margot James",,"2016-12-13T17:10:24.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657461/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657461/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657461/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-12-07","Temporary Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent representations he has received on the status and rights of agency workers.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","907835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657462","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-13","<p>Supporting businesses in the Northern Powerhouse is a priority for this Government.</p><p> </p><p>At the Autumn Statement, we launched the Northern Powerhouse strategy, setting out our strategic vision for an even stronger, more productive northern economy. Across the North we are supporting investment funds totalling over £500m for SMEs, investing £3.4billion in Growth Deal projects, and have created seventeen Enterprise Zones.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2016-12-13T17:16:10.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657462/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657462/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/657462/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-12-07","Regional Planning and Development: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps he is taking to support businesses as part of the Northern Powerhouse.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","907832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652577","Attorney General","false","2016-12-12","<p>There are no unpaid internships in the Law Officers Departments.</p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2016-12-12T15:46:32.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652577/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652577/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652577/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2016-12-06","Attorney General: Work Experience","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many unpaid internships there are in the Law Officers' Departments.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","56300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652578","Cabinet Office","false","2016-12-13","<p>In central London, of 181 offices in 2010, only 54 remain. Increased mobility and flexibility will further reduce demand for office space in central London as fewer staff need to be in offices full-time. Rationalisation will continue, enabling more multi-departmental use of HQ buildings and for civil servants to move to Canary Wharf and Croydon where property costs are lower.</p><p>We plan to move to around 20 efficient, fit-for-purpose buildings in central London by 2025, supported by smarter working.</p><p>Any proposed relocation is done based on the operational needs of individual departments, and each individual department is responsible for determining workforce numbers remaining in central London.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-12-13T09:24:25.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652578/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652578/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652578/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-12-06","Civil Servants: Location","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether his Department plans to relocate civil servants outside of central London as part of the 2018 move to 10 South Colonnade.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","56338"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652579","Cabinet Office","false","2016-12-12","<p>Officials of the Cabinet Office have held frequent and extensive meetings with our appointed advisors and with Barclays and their advisors since late 2015 to agree commercial terms of the lease assignment of 10 South Colonnade from Barclays to Cabinet Office. Discussions held were commercial in confidence.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-12-12T09:23:00.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652579/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652579/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652579/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-12-06","Civil Servants: Location","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what meetings have taken place between officials of his Department and Barclays representatives on the proposed move of 5,700 civil and public service posts to 10 South Colonnade.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","56349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652580","Cabinet Office","false","2016-12-12","<p>The List of Ministerial Responsibilities sets out the individual responsibilities of Government Ministers and departments. It also provides details of Non-Ministerial departments and Executive Agencies. It is for individual departments to determine the level of contact details to be provided, and they try to be as helpful as possible. When errors are identified, they are corrected on the online version. An updated hard copy version will be issued in due course.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","56410 ; 56411","2016-12-12T16:22:00.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652580/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652580/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652580/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-12-06","List of Ministerial Responsibilities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, for what reasons the Cabinet Office List of Ministerial Responsibilities published in October 2016 does not have Ministers' Private Office email addresses in all cases but rather generic email addresses; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Simon Burns","Chelmsford","Sir Simon Burns","56412"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652581","Cabinet Office","false","2016-12-12","<p>The List of Ministerial Responsibilities sets out the individual responsibilities of Government Ministers and departments. It also provides details of Non-Ministerial departments and Executive Agencies. It is for individual departments to determine the level of contact details to be provided, and they try to be as helpful as possible. When errors are identified, they are corrected on the online version. An updated hard copy version will be issued in due course.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","56411 ; 56412","2016-12-12T16:22:00.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652581/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652581/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652581/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-12-06","List of Ministerial Responsibilities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, when his Department plans to correct contact detail inaccuracies in the List of Ministerial Responsibilities published in October 2016.","false","Biography information for Sir Simon Burns","Chelmsford","Sir Simon Burns","56410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652583","Cabinet Office","false","2016-12-12","<p>The List of Ministerial Responsibilities sets out the individual responsibilities of Government Ministers and departments. It also provides details of Non-Ministerial departments and Executive Agencies. It is for individual departments to determine the level of contact details to be provided, and they try to be as helpful as possible. When errors are identified, they are corrected on the online version. An updated hard copy version will be issued in due course.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","56410 ; 56412","2016-12-12T16:22:00.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652583/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652583/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652583/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-12-06","List of Ministerial Responsibilities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, for what reasons the Cabinet Office List of Ministerial Responsibilities published in October 2016 does not have Ministers' Private Office telephone numbers in all cases but rather switchboard numbers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Simon Burns","Chelmsford","Sir Simon Burns","56411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652584","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-12","<p>The Government will publish an impact assessment on the increase in the National Living Wage and the increases in the National Minimum Wage rates announced at Autumn Statement in due course.</p><p>The Low Pay Commission also evaluates the impact of the various rates upon both employers and workers, drawing on economic, labour market and pay analysis, independent research and stakeholder evidence. Their report can be found at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-minimum-wage-low-pay-commission-autumn-2016-report" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-minimum-wage-low-pay-commission-autumn-2016-report</a>.</p><p>From April 2017 all National Minimum Wage rates, and the National Living Wage, will be increased by more than inflation. The main rate (for 21 – 24 year olds) is expected, at that point, to be at its highest ever level in real terms.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","56281","2016-12-12T11:30:18.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652584/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652584/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652584/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-12-06","Minimum Wage: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will make an estimate of the potential effect of businesses paying the adult minimum wage rate to people under 25 years of age who are not in training but carrying out the same work as those 25 years of age or over on (a) rates of poverty and (b) levels of disposable income for people under 25 years of age.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","56280"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652585","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2016-12-12","<p>The Government will publish an impact assessment on the increase in the National Living Wage and the increases in the National Minimum Wage rates announced at Autumn Statement in due course.</p><p>The Low Pay Commission also evaluates the impact of the various rates upon both employers and workers, drawing on economic, labour market and pay analysis, independent research and stakeholder evidence. Their report can be found at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-minimum-wage-low-pay-commission-autumn-2016-report" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-minimum-wage-low-pay-commission-autumn-2016-report</a>.</p><p>From April 2017 all National Minimum Wage rates, and the National Living Wage, will be increased by more than inflation. The main rate (for 21 – 24 year olds) is expected, at that point, to be at its highest ever level in real terms.</p>","Stourbridge","Margot James","56280","2016-12-12T11:30:18.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652585/answer","Biography information for Margot James","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652585/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652585/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2016-12-06","Minimum Wage: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, if he will make an estimate of the cost to businesses of their paying the adult minimum wage rate to people under 25 years of age who are not in training but are doing the same job as people 25 years of age or older.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","56281"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652586","HM Treasury","false","2016-12-12","<p>There are no unpaid internships in HM Treasury</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-12-12T14:56:41.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652586/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652586/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652586/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-12-06","Treasury: Work Experience","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many unpaid internships there are in his Department.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","56314"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652587","HM Treasury","false","2016-12-14","<p>There are two publications which are published as part of the Government’s commitment to Transparency which contain information on travel and subsistence for Senior Officials and Ministers.</p><p>These can be found on the Gov.uk website following the links below:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/senior-officials-expenses" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/senior-officials-expenses</a></p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/hmt-ministers-meetings-hospitality-gifts-and-overseas-travel</a></p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2016-12-14T15:57:08.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652587/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652587/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652587/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-12-06","Treasury: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how much his Department spent on travel that was not standard class in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","56237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652588","HM Treasury","false","2016-12-13","<p>The latest statistics published by HM Revenue and Customs project that the top one per cent of income taxpayers will pay 26.9% of all income tax receipts this year, higher than in any year prior to 2010-11. The Government will continue to keep the taxation of high earners under review to ensure it is fair, incentivises hard work and contributes towards the long-term sustainability of the tax system.</p><p>The percentage share of income tax liabilities in 2020-21 (27.0%) is estimated from the published information for the 2013-14 Survey of Personal Incomes. This data has been projected using the economic assumptions consistent with the Office for Budget Responsibility’s November 2016 Economic and fiscal outlook.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-12-13T15:37:02.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652588/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652588/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652588/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-12-06","Income Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what proportion of income tax is estimated to come from the top one per cent of earners in the UK in 2020.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","56250"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652589","HM Treasury","false","2016-12-12","<p>There will continue to be levy free alternatives available, such as fruit juice and glucose tablets. The Government has also exempted Foods for Specific Groups from the levy, which ensures that certain foods for medicinal purposes will remain levy free.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-12-12T15:02:41.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652589/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652589/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652589/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-12-06","Soft Drinks: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to his Department's policy paper, entitled Soft Drinks Industry Levy, published on 5 December 2016, what the alternative levy free options are for people with Type 1 or Type 2 diabetes affected by the proposed soft drinks industry levy.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","56251"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652590","HM Treasury","false","2016-12-12","<p>The Government values the strong relationship between the UK and Jersey and Guernsey. HM Treasury officials meet with their counterparts from Jersey and Guernsey regularly to discuss issues of mutual interest, including the need for strong regulation and tax transparency.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-12-12T14:36:41.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652590/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652590/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652590/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-12-06","Economic Policy: Channel Islands","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 30 November 2016 to Question 54118, what assessment his Department has made of the net benefit to the UK economy of Jersey and Guernsey setting independent economic and taxation policies.","false","Biography information for Andrew Rosindell","Romford","Andrew Rosindell","56258"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652591","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-03-20","<p>In relation to your request at (a) and (b) the information requested is held by the Department and I will place a copy of these documents in the Library of the House. No oral submissions were made to the Department.</p><p>In relation to your request at (c), officials from the Department met with Birmingham City Council on 23 June 2016 at which the Council delivered a presentation and I will also place a copy of this document in the Library of the House.</p><p>Some information has been redacted. The information is the personal data, as defined by the Data Protection Act 1998 (DPA), of another individual.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-03-20T11:28:51.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652591/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652591/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652591/answer","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652591/answer/previousversion/26187","Biography information for Lord Barwell","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-12-06","Planning Permission: Birmingham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, whether, when making the decision to withdraw the direction for Birmingham City Council not to take any step in connection with the adoption of the Birmingham Development Plan 2031, his Department (a) received any submissions, whether oral or in writing, from third parties, (b) received any submissions from parties interested in or connected to the Peddimore Employment Site and Langley Sustainable Urban Extension and (c) held any meetings with third parties in relation to the decision to withdraw the Holding Direction.","false","Biography information for Mr Andrew Mitchell","Sutton Coldfield","Mr Andrew Mitchell","56249"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652592","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-12-14","<p>We recently conducted a consultation on our approach to the implementation of 100% Business Rates Retention. There were over 450 responses from local authorities, businesses interests and other organisations. My officials are currently considering these and we will publish a summary of the responses and our proposed way forward in due course. In the meantime, we will continue close collaboration with local government in taking this work forward, including through the Business Rates Retention Steering Group, which is jointly chaired by the Local Government Association and the Department for Communities and Local Government.</p><p>The Steering Group was established to consider the mechanisms needed to set up and run the new business rates system, as well as the timetable and implementation of the reforms. It oversees the work of a set of technical working groups, each looking at particular aspects of the reforms. The Group meets on a regular basis and has done so on 7 occasions since April 2016. All papers for meetings are published here: <a href="http://www.local.gov.uk/business-rates" target="_blank">http://www.local.gov.uk/business-rates</a></p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-12-14T15:03:48.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652592/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652592/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652592/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-12-06","Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what progress his Department has made on enabling local authorities to retain 100 per cent of business rates.","false","Biography information for Mr Peter Bone","Wellingborough","Mr Peter Bone","56271"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652593","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-03-28","<p>The Department's travel data is published on Gov.uk and can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dclg-ministerial-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dclg-ministerial-data</a></p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2017-03-28T14:07:14.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652593/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652593/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652593/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-12-06","Department for Communities and Local Government: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much his Department spent on travel that was not standard class in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","56226"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652594","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-12-14","<p>From 2013/14 the Department has directly funded various innovative projects, each with different delivery models to engage isolated adults with poor or no English who had not previously accessed mainstream training. By March 2017, these projects will have supported over 39,800 isolated adults to learn English.</p><p>We do not hold figures on the average number of hours of tuition undertaken as training may vary dependent on need and in some instances includes online resources as well as guided learning.</p><p>Prior to 2013/14 the Department's funding to support delivery of English language was channelled via the Skills Funding Agency to Further Education colleges and other providers in areas facing significant integration challenges. The Department does not hold figures on the number of learners undertaking lessons or the average length of tuition.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","56335","2016-12-14T15:02:01.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652594/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652594/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652594/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-12-06","English Language: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many hours of learning were provided on average to people undertaking lessons in English as a second language as a result of courses funded by his Department in each year since 2008-09.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","56334"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652595","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-12-14","<p>From 2013/14 the Department has directly funded various innovative projects, each with different delivery models to engage isolated adults with poor or no English who had not previously accessed mainstream training. By March 2017, these projects will have supported over 39,800 isolated adults to learn English.</p><p>We do not hold figures on the average number of hours of tuition undertaken as training may vary dependent on need and in some instances includes online resources as well as guided learning.</p><p>Prior to 2013/14 the Department's funding to support delivery of English language was channelled via the Skills Funding Agency to Further Education colleges and other providers in areas facing significant integration challenges. The Department does not hold figures on the number of learners undertaking lessons or the average length of tuition.</p><p> </p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","56334","2016-12-14T15:02:01.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652595/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652595/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652595/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-12-06","English Language: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many people his Department has helped to learn English as a second language as a result of courses funded by his Department in each year since 2008-09.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","56335"
