"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652644","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-13","<p>There are no unpaid internships within the Department for the Environment, Food and Rural Affairs.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-12-13T14:47:24.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652644/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652644/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-06","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Work Experience","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many unpaid internships there are in her Department.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","56305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652645","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-12","<p>Defra has no plans to introduce mandatory method of production labelling to highlight grass fed or pasture based systems of production, but supports the development of voluntary labelling and accreditation schemes that aim to promote and encourage welfare friendly approaches to farm animal husbandry.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-12-12T10:27:35.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652645/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652645/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-06","Dairy Products: Labelling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans she has to introduce food labelling for pasture-based milk and dairy products.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","56276"
