"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652310","Department for Education","false","2016-12-09","<p>The Department is not providing separate financial support to secondary schools for summer schools programmes, but schools can draw on their wider budgets to fund such provision.</p><p>Schools can prioritise support for disadvantaged pupils making the transition from primary to secondary school, including summer school programmes, through use of their pupil premium funding.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","56181","2016-12-09T11:31:29.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652310/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652310/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652310/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-12-05","Summer Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what financial assistance is available from the public purse to secondary schools seeking to run a summer school programme for disadvantaged pupils.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","56180"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652311","Department for Education","false","2016-12-09","<p>The Department is not providing separate financial support to secondary schools for summer schools programmes, but schools can draw on their wider budgets to fund such provision.</p><p>Schools can prioritise support for disadvantaged pupils making the transition from primary to secondary school, including summer school programmes, through use of their pupil premium funding.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","56180","2016-12-09T11:31:29.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652311/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652311/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652311/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-12-05","Summer Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what financial support her Department plans to offer secondary schools which provide summer school programmes for pupils transitioning from primary school to secondary school for September 2017.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","56181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652312","Department for Education","false","2016-12-15","<p>There are 32 people who have qualifications in human resources currently working in Human Resources roles in the Department for Education.</p><p> </p><p>All candidates selected into Human Resources roles have prior experience relevant to the role.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-12-15T10:11:05Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652312/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652312/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652312/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-12-05","Department for Education: Personnel Management","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many people employed in human resources roles in her Department have (a) prior experience and (b) qualifications in human resources.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","56113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652313","Department for Education","false","2016-12-13","<p>The Government published its response to the Early Years National Funding Formula consultation on 1 December. The response contains a thorough analysis of responses to each of the questions and can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/early-years-funding-changes-to-funding-for-3-and-4-year-olds" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/early-years-funding-changes-to-funding-for-3-and-4-year-olds</a></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2016-12-13T16:17:15.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652313/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652313/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652313/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-12-05","Pre-school Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will publish all the submissions to her Department's consultation, Early years funding: changes to funding for three and four-year olds.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","56058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652314","Department for Transport","false","2016-12-08","<p>Storm Angus did not warrant the mobilisation of the UK’s national resources nor the military to be deployed. However the Environment Agency, emergency services, Highways England, Network Rail and local highway authorities in affected areas were on standby to assist those that were affected and to also ensure that infrastructure was protected as much as possible.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2016-12-08T17:00:01.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652314/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652314/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652314/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-12-05","Storms","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what mobilisation of the UK's national resources took place during Storm Angus; which bridges were so protected during that Storm; what infrastructure was so protected during that Storm; and whether the Army was called to provide assistance during that Storm.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","56063"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652315","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-08","<p>The Government is in the process of reviewing the animal establishments licensing schemes, including those that regulate the sale of pet animals. We have proposed to replace the Pet Animals Act 1951 with regulations made under the Animal Welfare Act 2006. One of our proposals is to remove the exemption whereby someone can sell any number of pedigree animals without a licence if they have been bred from the family pet.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-12-08T14:36:37.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652315/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652315/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652315/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Cats: Animal Breeding","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether her Department plans to bring forward proposals to amend the Pet Animals Act 1951 to prohibit repeat breeding and sale from the family cat or cats.","false","Biography information for Rob Marris","Wolverhampton South West","Rob Marris","56069"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652316","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-08","<p>Storm Angus brought widespread heavy rainfall to many parts of the country, particularly across the South West and North East. During the storm the Environment Agency deployed 94m of temporary flood barriers and 2 small mobile water pumps. No incident command vehicles were deployed.</p><p> </p><p>1,095 staff were deployed to respond to the flooding and support affected communities. 139 Flood Warnings and 1 Severe Flood Warning were also issued.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-12-08T15:35:52.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652316/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652316/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652316/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Flood Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether temporary flood barriers, mobile water pumps and incident command vehicles were deployed during Storm Angus.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","56064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652317","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-08","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the reply given to the hon. Member for Sunderland Central, Julie Elliott, on 25 November 2016, PQ UIN 54005.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-12-08T14:30:21.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652317/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652317/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652317/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she plans to take to ensure that the UK meets the EU target to reuse and recycle 50 per cent of household waste by 2020.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","56065"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652318","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-12","<p>(a) Records of prior Human Resource experience for people employed in human resources roles in the Civil Service are not held centrally within Defra. The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p>(b) There are a total of 35 Human Resource staff in Defra who hold a Chartered Institute of Personnel &amp; Development (CIPD) Human resource qualification and a further seven staff are currently studying for a CIPD Human Resource qualification. Details of other qualifications in human resources are not centrally held and the information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-12-12T09:24:05.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652318/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652318/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652318/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Personnel Management","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many people employed in human resources roles in her Department have (a) prior experience and (b) qualifications in human resources.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","56114"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652319","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-08","<p>CAP payment data held for the 2015 European Commission financial year (16 October 2014 – 15 October 2015) is published on the UK CAP payments website.</p><p>The link is <a href="http://cap-payments.defra.gov.uk/Search.aspx" target="_blank">http://cap-payments.defra.gov.uk/Search.aspx</a>.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-12-08T12:02:33.1Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652319/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652319/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652319/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much each of the top 50 recipients of funding from the Common Agricultural Policy received in 2015.","false","Biography information for Lord Mann","Bassetlaw","John Mann","56079"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652320","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-08","<p>Defra has no plans to establish a Land Reform Review Group for England.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-12-08T14:40:53.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652320/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652320/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652320/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Land: Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will establish a Land Reform Review Group for England.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","56080"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652321","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-08","<p>There is no legal definition of “grass-fed“ in relation to livestock rearing practice, although there is a general obligation in food labelling and consumer law that food labelling should not mislead the consumer and this obligation remains in place. Previous voluntary labelling guidance defined grass-fed as “fed primarily on grass in the field”.</p><p> </p><p>Defra is currently working on a range of proposals to inform discussions about the shape of a future agriculture policy and we want to ensure that the future regulatory framework continues to provide consumers with confidence in the food that they are buying, and continues to secure our world-leading reputation for high quality and standards.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-12-08T15:52:54.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652321/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652321/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652321/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Meat: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what definition her Department uses of the term grass-fed; and what guidance her Department issues to farmers on the use of the term grass-fed when marketing meat.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","56081"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652322","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-08","<p>The Government has invested £2.5 billion over six years on improving flood defences to better protect over 300,000 homes. This is a real terms increase in capital investment – up from £1.7 billion in the last Parliament and £1.5 billion between 2005 and 2010.</p><p> </p><p>The table below summarises the total capital investment on flood and coastal risk management for St Helens, Merseyside and England for each year since 2010.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan="2"><p> </p></td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>Total capital investment on flood and coastal risk management (£k) </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>St Helens (Metropolitan Borough) </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Merseyside</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>England</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>318</p></td><td><p>4,501</p></td><td><p>363,985</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>188</p></td><td><p>1,329</p></td><td><p>321,900</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>377</p></td><td><p>466</p></td><td><p>323,219</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>78</p></td><td><p>380,217</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>206</p></td><td><p>507,884</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>412,952</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-12-08T17:01:19.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652322/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652322/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652322/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Flood Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much funding has been allocated to (a) St Helens, (b) Merseyside and (c) the UK for flood prevention and remediation in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","56073"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652323","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-08","<p>The Department provides funding for flood risk management projects through Grant in Aid to Risk Management Authorities, which include the Environment Agency, local authorities and internal drainage boards. Please see the attached table which shows Grant in Aid funding allocated to Risk Management Authorities in 2016/17. This is a snapshot for the current year and reflects the bids made by authorities for specific projects.</p><p> </p><p>In addition funding for local authorities’ ongoing flood prevention responsibilities is provided through the Local Government Settlement. Local authorities have freedom to determine their own priorities and so there is no specific flood allocation by authority.</p><p> </p><p>Funding for two ongoing flood responsibilities, the Lead Local Flood Authority role and local authorities’ role as statutory consultee on surface water for major developments, was previously provided through Defra and DCLG grants but as of 2016/17 has been fully rolled into the settlement. The visible lines show a notional amount for each authority for these two purposes. The lines indicate the priority central government gives to these two services but do not affect authorities’ freedom to set their own priorities locally.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-12-08T15:00:59.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652323/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652323/answer","Grant in Aid funding allocated to Risk Management Authorities.pdf","Grant in Aid funding allocated to Risk Management Authorities.pdf","Grant in Aid funding allocated to Risk Management ","Grant in Aid funding allocated to Risk Management ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652323/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Flood Control","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much funding for flood prevention her Department has allocated to each local authority in 2016-17.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","56074"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652324","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-13","<p>Defra’s Code of Recommendations for pigs, which all pig-keepers must be familiar with, provides guidance on how to comply with the legal requirements in relation to environmental enrichment and routine tail-docking. When carrying out an inspection of a pig unit, the Animal Health and Plant Health Agency evaluate the provision of enrichment material and whether pigs are routinely tail-docked without a justifiable reason and will apply breaches where non-compliances are found.</p><p> </p><p>There are health and welfare reasons for continuing to tail-dock in certain circumstances, but we and the pig industry recognise a need to improve the quality of enrichment materials available for all pigs and increase opportunities to stop tail-docking.</p><p> </p><p>Defra contributed to a European Commission research project by Bristol University which informed the EU Commission’s recently published guidance on tail docking and enrichment materials. We are working with the industry to implement these recommendations on tail docking and enrichment which were published earlier this year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-12-13T17:56:03.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652324/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652324/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652324/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Pigs: Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to improve enforcement of (a) paragraph 15 on environmental enrichment for pigs of Schedule 8 to the Aftercare of Farmed Animals (England) Regulations 2007 and (b) paragraph 5 on tail docking of pigs of Schedule 3 to the Mutilations (Permitted Procedures) (England) Regulations 2007.","false","Biography information for Sir Alan Meale","Mansfield","Sir Alan Meale","56158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652325","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-08","<p>Further to PQ 55450, the reasons for refusal to grant import permits are as follows:</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong>9</strong> applications were refused because APHA asked for additional information regarding the specimens. As there was no response from applicant the applications were closed and refused.</p><p> </p><p><strong>2</strong> applications were refused because of irregularities surrounding the weight of the specimens (tusks).</p><p> </p><p><strong>1</strong> application was withdrawn and therefore formally refused.</p><p> </p><p><strong>1</strong> application refused as a permit was not required for the requested activity. Personal effects derogation applied.</p><p> </p><p><strong>7</strong> applications refused because imports to the EU of ivory from the source specified in the application is prohibited.</p><p> </p><p><strong>20</strong> applications refused because they were retrospective.</p><p> </p><p><strong>1</strong> application refused as APHA could not be satisfied the specimen was pre-convention.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2016-12-08T14:44:03.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652325/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652325/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652325/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Ivory: Imports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 2 December 2016 to Question 55450, if she will publish the reasons why the Animal and Plant Health Agency refused to grant import permits in those cases; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","56145"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652326","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-12-08","<p>Protecting our country from pests and diseases is important for our economy, the environment and our health and we will continue to monitor the situation and work with farmers to limit the damage to our valuable crops sector.</p><p> </p><p>Diamondback moths migrate to the UK every summer. While the number observed this year was particularly high, a range of control methods is available for farmers to protect their crops, including through application of the pesticide Benevia 10OD. The Government issued an emergency authorisation for the use of this pesticide to combat the moth earlier this year.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-12-08T15:40:27.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652326/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652326/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652326/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-12-05","Moths: Crops","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to prevent diamondback moths from destroying seasonal Brussels sprouts crops.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","56210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652327","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-12-12","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not hold any information on this issue.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-12-12T15:13:52.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652327/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652327/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652327/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-05","Israel: Courts Martial","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what information the Government holds on whether any UK nationals sit as judges in Israeli military courts.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","56157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652328","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-12-12","<p>​We remain concerned about the human rights situation in Eritrea, including the arrest and continued detention of politicians, journalists and religious figures. FCO officials regularly press the Government of Eritrea to fulfil its international human rights obligations. We will continue to work with the international community to address ongoing human rights concerns in Eritrea as set out by the Early Day Motion (EDM) 504 of Session 2015-16.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-12-12T15:57:18.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652328/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652328/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652328/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-05","Eritrea: Political Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to Early Day Motion (EDM) 504 of Session 2015-16, Prisoners of Conscience in Eritrea, if he will meet with the Eritrean Ambassador to the UK to discuss the cases of Dawit Isaal, Aster Fissehatsion and the other political prisoners referred to in that EDM.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","56143"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652329","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-12-12","<p>Our close relationship with the United Arab Emirates (UAE) allows us to discuss important issues such as Human Rights and where the UK has cause for concern we raise it at official and Ministerial level. The 2017 UK-UAE Year of Culture presents an excellent opportunity for strengthening and developing dialogue between our two countries.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-12-12T15:46:42.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652329/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652329/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652329/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-05","United Arab Emirates: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, whether the Government plans to raise reports of human rights violations in the United Arab Emirates during the 2017 UK-UAE Year of Culture.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","56107"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652330","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-12-12","<p>​We are unable to give information on the number of British nationals that have reported rape to the Emirati authorities. Due to the low numbers involved, this may lead to individuals being identifiable.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-12-12T15:48:26.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652330/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652330/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652330/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-05","United Arab Emirates: Rape","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many British women were arrested for reporting rape in the United Arab Emirates (a) between 2011 and 2016 and (b) during 2016.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","56108"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652331","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-12-08","<p>Getting humanitarian supplies to the nearly 1 million people living in the besieged areas in Syria, including eastern Aleppo, is a priority for this Government. The Foreign Secretary, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Uxbridge and South Ruislip (Mr Johnson) discusses the issue of humanitarian access with international partners on a regular basis. He spoke to US Secretary of State, John Kerry, about the humanitarian situation in Syria most recently during a telephone call on 20 November. They also discussed these issues with like-minded partners during the meeting convened by the Foreign Secretary in London on 16 October. These high-level discussions have not gone into detail on specific types of technology. At working level the UK is working closely with the US and UN on possible options to get aid into besieged areas.</p><p>We continue to support the UN's efforts to get humanitarian supplies to people across Syria. This is most effectively done by road. Airdrops are more dangerous and harder to implement successfully than ground access. In many cases, aid is just a few miles away from those in besieged areas and could reach people in need if the Syrian regime allowed UN road convoys in. This is true in eastern Aleppo where the opposition has agreed the UN's four point plan. We continue to urge the regime to agree it too; and we press Russia and Iran to use their influence with the regime to make this happen urgently.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-12-08T15:13:09.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652331/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652331/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652331/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-05","Syria: International Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what discussions he has had with (a) his US counterpart and (b) the UN on the potential use of the Joint Precision Airdrop System to deliver humanitarian relief supplies to (i) Aleppo and (ii) elsewhere in Syria.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","56103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652332","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","true","2016-12-16","<p>Records of fines in the Territory only date back to 2013. There have been no fines issued for the damage of property during this time. In 201<ins class="ministerial">5</ins><del class="ministerial">4</del> a building on Diego Garcia was damaged. The perpetrators paid for the repairs and so were not prosecuted.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-12-16T14:03:59.9Z","2017-03-23T17:19:58.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652332/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652332/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652332/answer","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652332/answer/previousversion/26971","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-05","British Indian Ocean Territory: Fines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 2 December 2016 to Question 54666, how many fines have been issued to those caught damaging buildings in the British Indian Ocean Territory for each year in the last 30 years for which records are available; and what the (a) individual and (b) total amount of such fines was in each such year.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","56089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652333","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-12-16","<p>The licence to own and operate internal communications services from Diego Garcia was granted to Cable &amp; Wireless in 1982 (subsequently Batelco / Sure in 2013, following a corporate split of Cable &amp; Wireless, then purchased by Batelco) and provides a five year notice of termination. The British Indian Ocean Territory (BIOT) Commissioner served notice of termination to Sure in March 2014, after which the BIOT Administration will be reprocuring the licence. The value of the licence is commercially sensitive.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-12-16T14:12:23.52Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652333/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652333/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652333/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-05","British Indian Ocean Territory: Sure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 2 December 2016 to Question 54664, when the contract between Sure telecoms and the British Indian Ocean Territory Administration was agreed; when that contract will next be tendered for; and what the value is of that contract.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","56090"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652334","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-12-16","<p>While there have been no attacks around the waters of the British Indian Ocean Territory, piracy is a significant threat in the Gulf of Aden and Indian Ocean, and has occurred as far as 1,000 nautical miles from the coast of Somalia. We undertake regular assessments of potential criminal activity in the territorial waters of the British Indian Ocean Territory in order to ensure that we retain an appropriate level of capability.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-12-16T14:10:46.24Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652334/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652334/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652334/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-05","British Indian Ocean Territory: Piracy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the risk of piracy in the waters of the British Indian Ocean Territory.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","56091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652335","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-12-13","<p>We do not centrally hold details of how many officials at the Foreign and Commonwealth Office have prior experience of working in human resources. To provide you with this would require us to gather information from the personnel file of each staff member and the cost of doing this would be disproportionate and exceed the appropriate limit. We do, however, hold a record of those staff currently employed in the Human Resources Directorate as at 8<sup>th</sup> November 2016 who</p><p>(a) are members of the Civil Service HR Profession, with a career anchor in HR : 12 staff.</p><p>(b) are not members of the Civil Service HR Profession or have a career anchor in HR but who have a CIPD (or equivalent HR qualification) : 15 staff.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2016-12-13T17:45:56.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652335/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652335/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652335/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-12-05","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Personnel Management","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many people employed in human resources roles in his Department have (a) prior experience and (b) qualifications in human resources.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","56115"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652336","Department of Health","false","2016-12-13","<p>The expansion to the NHS Graduate Management Training Scheme which was announced by my Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health on 30 November will be funded from within existing National Health Service budgets.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-12-13T10:25:40.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652336/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652336/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652336/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-12-05","NHS: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans his Department has to fund the expansion of the NHS graduate management scheme; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","56061"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652337","Department of Health","false","2016-12-07","<p>Data for available and occupied paediatric critical care beds, for the week ending 4 December 2016, will be published as part of the winter weekly sitreps on NHS England’s website on 9 December 2016 at 9.30am.</p><p> </p><p>The data will be available at the link below:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/winter-daily-sitreps/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/winter-daily-sitreps/</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-12-07T15:08:57.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652337/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652337/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652337/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-12-05","Paediatrics: Intensive Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many paediatric intensive care beds were free and available for use on 3 and 4 December 2016 in NHS hospitals in England.","false","Biography information for Christian Matheson","City of Chester","Christian Matheson","56059"
