"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652339","Department of Health","false","2016-12-13","<p>The information requested about the status of people admitted to accident and emergency units with flu is not routinely collected.</p><p> </p><p>The number of people vaccinated against flu in financial years 2009/10-2015/16 is set out in the table.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Flu Season</p></td><td><p>Estimated number of persons vaccinated</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009/10</p></td><td><p>10,308,522</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>11,214,949</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>11,735,081</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>11,948,206</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>12,723,280</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>13,306,979</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>14,080,238</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Notes:</em></p><ol><li>Data is taken from the annual Seasonal flu vaccine uptake reports.</li><li>‘Number of persons vaccinated’ comprises the total general practitioner (GP)-registered population vaccinated, vaccinated healthcare workers, and children vaccinated as part of the schools programme in 2015/16.</li><li>Data on vaccinations given to pregnant women first became available in 2010/11, therefore the figure for 2009/10 does not include pregnancy vaccinations.</li><li>The period covered is 1 September to 31 January for each flu season apart from 2014/15 and 2015/16 when data for Healthcare Workers was to the end of February.</li><li>Due to the nature of the data collections there is some minor duplication leading to a possible over-estimation of vaccines given as those vaccines given to healthcare workers and children in Years 1 and 2 (five and six year olds) in 2015/16 may/may not have been recorded in the GP record. Conversely in 2015/16 as a result of at risk groups being able to access flu vaccination in pharmacies for the first time some vaccine given to this group may not have been recorded in the GP record. These are known data issues related to data flows into the GP record.</li><li>The flu programme was extended to all children aged two and three year olds in 2013/14; all four year olds in 2014/15; and all those of primary school age children of Years 1 and 2 (five and six year olds) in 2015/16.</li></ol>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","56169","2016-12-13T16:36:33.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652339/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652339/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652339/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-12-05","Accident and Emergency Departments: Influenza","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people admitted to accident and emergency departments for flu were (a) pregnant, (b) suffering from a long-term health condition and (c) 65 years and over in each calendar year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Mrs Sharon Hodgson","Washington and Sunderland West","Mrs Sharon Hodgson","56056"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652340","Department of Health","false","2016-12-09","<p>The numbers of people employed in human resources (HR) roles in the core Department who have prior HR experience are set out in the table below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Overall HR experience</p></td><td><p>Number</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Less than 1 year</p></td><td><p>5 or fewer</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 to 10 years</p></td><td><p>13</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>10 to 20 years</p></td><td><p>18</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>20 to 40 years</p></td><td><p>11</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Of the above people, 22 individuals have formal qualifications in HR–related subjects.</p><p>This number does not include those in the Department’s HR directorate who are currently working towards formal qualifications in HR-related subjects.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-12-09T10:21:53.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652340/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652340/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652340/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-12-05","Department of Health: Personnel Management","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people employed in human resources roles in his Department have (a) prior experience and (b) qualifications in human resources.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","56116"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652341","Department of Health","false","2016-12-08","<p>We are working on developing a new tobacco control plan, which we will be publishing shortly. The plan will focus on supporting priority groups such as pregnant women and young people.</p><p> </p><p>The Tobacco and Related Products Regulations require tobacco producers (manufacturers and importers) to supply sales data annually for the whole of the United Kingdom alongside a range of other information when products are notified. Public Health England will make public all data that is not commercially sensitive.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","56083 ; 56085 ; 56086","2016-12-08T09:06:35.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652341/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652341/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/652341/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-12-05","Tobacco: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether his Department plans to require tobacco manufacturers to publish sales data at a local level; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alex Cunningham","Stockton North","Alex Cunningham","56082"
